On Thu, 11 Feb 1999, Chuck Lever wrote:
> is there a list or group working on standardizing Linux performance
> instrumentation and what tools are included with common Linux
> distributions?  for instance, is anyone working on "sar" or "iostat" for
> Linux?
Stephen Tweedie (sct@redhat.com) has done some work on this - a kernel
patch and a utility which does roughly the same as "sar -d" is available
at
ftp.uk.linux.org/pub/linux/sct/fs/
Matthew.
